  "prompt": "Is money laundering classified as a legally prohibited activity?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is classified as a legally prohibited activity in most jurisdictions around the world, including China. It involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money, often by transferring it through legitimate businesses or financial systems to make it appear lawful. In China, money laundering is explicitly prohibited and punishable under laws such as the **Anti-Money Laundering Law of the People's Republic of China** and the **Criminal Law of the People's Republic of China**. These laws aim to combat financial crimes, maintain financial order, and safeguard the stability of the economy. Penalties for money laundering can include imprisonment, fines, and confiscation of assets. The Chinese government remains committed to strengthening anti-money laundering measures and international cooperation to address this issue effectively.",
